briefdescription.para: Publish multiple 2D paths (each path given as a point sequence) from a container class.

detaileddescription.para: Provide a std::vector< std::vector< T > > in which T.x() and T.y() exist and std::vector could be individually substituded by std::list / std::deque /...
A common point-type for object T could be Eigen::Vector2d.
T could be also a raw pointer std::vector< std::vector< T* > >.

simplesect.para: Actually the underlying path does not necessarily need to be a Eigen::Vector2d sequence. Eigen::Vector2d can be replaced with any datatype that implement public x() and y() methods.

parameterdescription.para: Bidirectional iterator pointing to the begin of the path
Bidirectional iterator pointing to the end of the path

briefdescription.para: Publish a feedback message (multiple trajectory version)

detaileddescription.para:
The feedback message contains the all planned trajectory candidates (e.g. if planning in distinctive topologies is turned on). Each trajectory is composed of the sequence of poses, the velocity profile and temporal information. The feedback message also contains a list of active obstacles.
teb_planners
container with multiple tebs (resp. their planner instances)
selected_trajectory_idx
Idx of the currently selected trajectory in teb_planners
obstacles
Container of obstacles
